            <sense xml:id="Tmain" xml:lang="en" source="#traces"> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> ṣǝrḥ </t:quote></cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> chamber </t:quote></cit> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወይትገበር፡ ሰቀላ፡ አው፡ ጽርሕ፡ በአፍአ፡ ቅጽራ፡ ለይእቲ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን።</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> Let there be a shed or a hall constructed outside the fence of the concerned church </t:quote></cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Getatchew2013MeshafeBerhanT"/><citedRange unit="page"> 86 (ed.) </citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="bm:Getatchew2013MeshafeBerhanV"/><citedRange unit="page"> 59 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማዕፆ፡ ዐቢያን፡ ዘአናቅጽ፡ መንገለ፡ ዓረብ፡ በአፍአ፡ ፬ወበውሥጥ፡ ፬። ወጽርሕ፡ ፩። ሰሜናዊ፡ ፩። ወደቡባዊ፡ ፩።</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">On trouve de grandes fermetures en boix, aux portes, 4 à l’extérieur, vers l’ouest, et 4 à l’intérieur: il y en a une au ṣerḥ, une au nord, une au sud,</t:quote></cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1909LiberT"/><citedRange unit="page"> 7 l. 4–5 (ed.)</citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1910LiberV"/><citedRange unit="page"> 7 l. 9–12 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl> <sense n="L" xml:id="TL"><foreign xml:lang="gez">ጽርሕ</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">ṣǝrḥ</t:quote></cit>, <lbl expand="pluralis">Pl.</lbl> <foreign xml:lang="gez">አጽራሕ</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">ʾaṣrāḥ</t:quote></cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">chamber</t:quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">upper chamber</t:quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><t:quote xmlns:t="http:/